group.wikiBody:
The fourth album by the English rock band Led Zeppelin was released on 8 November 1971. Upon its release, Led Zeppelin IV was a commercial and critical success. In 2003, the album was ranked 66th on Rolling Stone magazine's list of "The 500 Greatest Albums of All Time".

  1. Black Dog (4:35)
  2. Rock And Roll (3:39)
  3. The Battle Of Evermore (5:51)
  4. Stairway To Heaven (7:58)
  5. Misty Mountain Hop (4:38)
  6. Four Sticks (4:44)
  7. Going To California (3:31)
  8. When The Levee Breaks (7:07)


Staff edit: Cassette Approval: The reel-to-reel version has been specifically approved as a high quality analogue source. irredentia

These are the 2 CDs of the 2014 edition of Led Zeppelin IV.

2. Rock And Roll (Alternate Mix)

5. Misty Mountain Hop (Alternate Mix)
